data.description: Welcome Home to this beautiful Craftsman style home that was built in 1908 in the heart of Campbellsville's Residential Historic District featuring 4 Bedrooms, 2.5 Baths, Hardwood flooring throughout, tall ceilings, beautiful wood trim, an Office or Den, a Formal Dining Room with built in corner hutch, a chef's kitchen featuring a gas stove with a pot filler, elegant cabinetry with tons of storage, Granite Countertops, Stainless Steel Appliances, a Trash Compactor, Garbage Disposal, a Pantry that also offers Laundry space, an Unfinished Basement, a cozy Living Room with a gas Fireplace, a stunning covered front porch with swing, a deck overlooking the large fenced in backyard, a detached 2 Car Garage with what could be a separate living quarters featuring 3 spacious rooms with 2 entrances.  This home is conveniently located within walking distance to Downtown Campbellsville, Miller Park, the City Lake and within 5  minutes to Taylor Regional Hospital and the prestigious Campbellsville University!!!
